[2]
Date: Sat 20 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: World Health Organisation (WHO) Disease Outbreaks Report, Fri
19 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/n2002/july/19ajuly2002.html>

El Salvador: Dengue/dengue Haemorrhagic Fever - WHO Update 2
------------------------------------------------------------
As of Sat 6 Jul 2002, the Ministry of Health of El Salvador has
reported 2249 cases of dengue fever including 6 deaths and 156 cases
of dengue haemorrhagic fever. The epidemic curve suggests the
outbreak has peaked.The Ministers of Health for El Salvador,
Guatemala and Honduras will be meeting soon to discuss strategies in
dengue surveillance, prevention and control.
******
[3]
Date: Sat 20 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: World Health Organisation (WHO) Disease Outbreaks Report, Fri
19 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/n2002/july/19bjuly2002.html>

Honduras: Dengue/dengue Haemorrhagic Fever
------------------------------------------
As of 29 Jun 2002, WHO has received reports of 3993 cases of dengue
fever including 8 deaths and 545 cases of dengue haemorrhagic fever.
The regions affected by dengue haemorrhagic fever are Francisco,
Morazan, La Paz, Cortes, Olancho, Comayagua, Choluteca, El Paraiso,
Yoro, Santa Barbara, and Copan.
The measures taken in response to the dengue outbreak in Honduras
focus on community participation, and communication strategies.
Coordination of efforts in bordering areas with El Salvador for
surveillance and vector control are being undertaken. The Ministers
of Health for El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras will be meeting
soon to discuss strategies in dengue surveillance, prevention and
control.
